Lets create a Repository in GitHub

-> New
->Repository
->Repository Name
->Title
->Click Create Repository

Cloning a repository
->Repository Name 
->Code
->Copy URL from Repository
->Open Git Bash
->Type "git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/YOUR-REPOSITORY"
->Enter (Local Clone would be created)

Adding a file to a repository using the command line

->Stage the file for commit to your local repository - $ git add .
->Commit the file that you've staged in your local repository - $ git commit -m "Add existing file"
->Push the changes in your local repository to GitHub.com - $ git push origin YOUR_BRANCH



